If you want to use this css:

```css
table.tablesorter thead tr .header {
    background-image: url(/Images/bg.gif);
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    background-position: center right;
    cursor: pointer;
}

/* ... */

table.tablesorter thead tr .headerSortUp {
    background-image: url(/Images/asc.gif);
}
table.tablesorter thead tr .headerSortDown {
    background-image: url(/Images/desc.gif);
}
table.tablesorter thead tr .headerSortDown, table.tablesorter thead tr .headerSortUp {
    background-color: #8dbdd8;
}
```

you'd need to change some of the default settings ([cssHeader](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#cssheader), [cssAsc](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#cssasc) &amp; [cssDesc](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#cssdesc)):

```js
$(function () {
    $('table').tablesorter({
        cssAsc    : 'headerSortUp',
        cssDesc   : 'headerSortDown',
        cssHeader : 'header',
    });
});
```

