@blagarde I don't believe `unicodecsv` is supposed to work on Python 3 as Python 3's `csv` module handles unicode properly. If you need to support Python 2 and 3, try this:
```python
import sys

is_python2 = sys.version_info[0] == 2

if is_python2:
    import unicodecsv as csv
else:
    import csv
```
Then, simply use the `csv` module. In Python 2, it will really use ``unicodecsv``.

