@StefanRijnhart This brings back the version parameter as per your initial docstring. A more detailed version is warranted as for example when openupgradelib is in a minor module migration series. being more detailed about the version avoids already the most common naming conflicts. However, there is an edge case which would be not covered by this: When I treat a foreign model, in one's modlu migration script, and then afterwards happen to treat the same model in another module with coinciding small version numbers, without doing a cleanup in the meantime. I think that's generally acceptable as being not supported, but minor version update series should come back.

Sidenote/Idea:
As the minor version would be available in the hopefully accepted Environment's context, I'm thinking of a way to decorate this function in order to keep the old signature, yet enable the use of the environment. I would guess that the Environment is managed by Environment.manage() and therefore calling it from the courser might retrieve the very same environment which holds the version info. If that would be possible we could easily overcharge several methods with an environment while fully remaining compatible with the old signature. This would mean that we would be possible to add this functionality magically all over the codebase without changing a single line of code...

